<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="525" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,870,2011]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,694,906,931]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">
<typeStatus box="[199,308,906,931]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Holotype</typeStatus>
description. Head and thorax.
</emphasis>
Structural features of head and thorax (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1318,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Figs. 53–54</figureCitation>
) much as described above for 
<taxonomicName box="[379,553,943,966]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[379,553,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">A. amazonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[560,649,942,967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[560,649,942,967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,870,2011]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,978,1003]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Color.</emphasis>
Crown, anterior margin of pronotum and mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[896,979,978,1003]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
) yellow with irregular reddish-brown or brown marks; disc of pronotum reddish-brown with yellow margins; mesonotum with apex pale yellow. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[159,294,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Figs. 53–54</figureCitation>
) reddish-brown, except for membranous portions. Face, lateral and ventral portions of thorax, and legs (
<figureCitation box="[159,241,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
) mostly yellow; superior portion of frons and of lateral lobe of pronotum brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="525" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,870,2011]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,383,1122,1147]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[508,598,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, strongly produced posteriorly; with distinct lobe on basiventral portion; disc with dispersed setae. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[878,1015,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Figs. 56–57</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, subtriangular; basal third slightly expanded laterally and then tapering toward apex; distal portion appearing articulated with remainder of plate (
<figureCitation box="[255,395,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Figs. 56–57</figureCitation>
); in lateral view, plates short, not extending posteriorly beyond basal half of pygofer; plate surface with scattered setae. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[615,698,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, T-shaped; stalk with median keel, apex distinctly expanded. Style (
<figureCitation box="[349,435,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, extending posteriorly much farther than apex of connective; preapical lobe distinct, bearing few setae; apical portion directed outward; apex acute. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1140,1275,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Figs. 59–60</figureCitation>
) symmetrical; shaft (
<figureCitation box="[221,305,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, elongate, sinuate, distal half slender and slightly curved dorsally, median third with small dentiform process; in ventral view, apex (
<figureCitation box="[681,762,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
) with pair of tiny processes directed laterally; aedeagal base with pair of conspicuous basal processes with their apices curved anterodorsally. Anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[1245,1331,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
) without processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,870,2011]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1518,1543]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Female</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[301,419,1518,1543]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[577,661,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, with basal, median bifurcated structure (
<collectionCode box="[1324,1379,1519,1543]" country="Suriname" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15705" name="University of Suriname" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">BBS</collectionCode>
) and pair of lateral, narrow elongate projections (LPR). Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[822,905,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, strongly produced posteriorly; apex obtuse; disc with dispersed setae. First valvifers (
<figureCitation box="[794,882,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, elongate, subrectangular. First valvulae (
<figureCitation box="[263,349,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with conspicuous basiventral lobe (BLB; 
<figureCitation box="[1027,1112,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
); with projection on median portion of ventral margin (VPR); apex acute, dentiform (
<figureCitation box="[790,928,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Figs. 64, 69</figureCitation>
); setae distributed on ventral margin of basal third and basiventral lobe; ventral interlocking device located on basal half of blade; dorsal sculptured area (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Figs. 66–67, 69</figureCitation>
) extending from basal portion of blade to apex, formed mostly by scale-like process arranged in oblique lines; ventral sculptured area (
<figureCitation box="[491,573,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
) restricted to apical portion of blade, formed mostly by scale-like processes. Second valvulae (
<figureCitation box="[359,446,1806,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with dorsal margin slightly convex; ventral margin almost straight; preapical prominence strong (
<figureCitation box="[491,578,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
); apex obtuse; about 27 teeth (
<figureCitation box="[932,1068,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Figs. 70–74</figureCitation>
) distributed on dorsal expanded portion of blade; most teeth (
<figureCitation box="[489,573,1878,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
) triangular, armed with denticles, with ascending portion (= anterior edge) short, descending portion (= posterior edge) elongate; blade with ducts (
<figureCitation box="[976,1114,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Figs. 72–73</figureCitation>
) extending to apical portion and to teeth or terminating below latter; few basal teeth (
<figureCitation box="[804,887,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[198,1346,249,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1396,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov., female. 62, sternite VII, ventral view; 63, pygofer, lateral view; 64, first valvifer and first valvula, lateral view; 65, basal lobe of first valvula; 66, dorsal sculptured area at basal portion of blade; 67, dorsal sculptured area at median portion of blade; 68, ventral sculptured area; 69, apical portion of blade; 70, second valvula, lateral view; 71, teeth at basal portion of blade; 72, teeth at median portion of blade; 73, teeth at apical portion of blade; 74, apical third of blade. Scale bars: 62 – 64, 70 = 1 mm. BBS: basimedian bifurcated structure, BLB: basal lobe, LPR: lateral projection, VPR: ventral projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437251/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
) without ducts. Gonoplacs, in lateral view, with basal half narrow and apical half distinctly expanded; apex obtuse.
</paragraph>
