<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="526" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1572,1705]" pageId="11" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1572,1597]" pageId="11" pageNumber="526">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species, 
<taxonomicName box="[690,757,1573,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis box="[690,757,1573,1596]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="526">tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, refers to the slender apical half of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1412,1435]" captionTargetBox="[191,1402,237,1357]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 61. Acrogonia tenuis sp. nov. 53, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsal view (total length 8.5 mm); 54, body, male holotype, lateral view; 55 – 61, male genitalia: 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, subgenital plates, ventral view; 57, subgenital plate and part of style, lateral view; 58, styles and connective, dorsal view; 59, aedeagus and its basal processes, lateral view; 60, aedeagus and its basal processes, ventral view; 61, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 55 = 1 mm; 56 – 61 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437250/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="526">Figs. 59– 60</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
